         <h1>Jester Hairston, 98, Choral Expert and Actor </h1>
           <div class="row">
               <div class="col-md-10">
 					<p class="text-left">
<blue>1</blue>Jester Hairston , a veteran character actor and a conductor and arranger who was praised as one of the leading authorities on black choral music , died Jan. 18 in Los Angeles . <br><blue>2</blue>He was 98 . <br><blue>3</blue>Mr. Hairston came to Hollywood in 1935 as the assistant conductor for the Hall Johnson choir , which had been hired to sing in the black-cast film '' The Green Pastures . '' <br><blue>4</blue>His musical break came when he met the composer Dimitri Tiomkin while conducting the Johnson choir as it recorded the background score for the movie '' Lost Horizon '' ( 1937 ) . <br><blue>5</blue>When a producer questioned the ability of black singers to perform in Russian , Mr. Tiomkin reportedly said , '' I do n't see color . <br><blue>6</blue>I hear music , '' and assured Mr. Hairston , '' If I come back to Hollywood , you are my choral conductor and arranger . '' <br><blue>7</blue>Mr. Tiomkin did return , and during the next 20 years , Mr. Hairston worked with him on films including '' Red River , '' '' She Wore a Yellow Ribbon , '' '' Duel in the Sun '' and '' Land of the Pharaohs . '' <br><blue>8</blue>He established himself as one of Hollywood 's most respected choral directors . <br><blue>9</blue>He continued working as a musical arranger after the partnership with Mr. Tiomkin ended . <br><blue>10</blue>He was best known for his work in '' Lilies of the Field , '' for which he composed and arranged the song '' Amen '' and dubbed the singing for Sidney Poitier . <br><blue>11</blue>He composed or arranged more than 300 choral spirituals . <br><blue>12</blue>Mr. Hairston supplemented his income as a conductor by accepting bit parts in Hollywood films and appearing in several Tarzan movies as an African . '' <br><blue>13</blue>They always picked me for the Tarzan films because my skin was so black , '' he told an interviewer . <br><blue>14</blue>He was harshly criticized for accepting stereotypical roles like that of Jethro , the slave of Jim Bowie in the 1960 film '' The Alamo , '' who , when freed by his master , insisted on remaining at his side . <br><blue>15</blue>And although he played the part of Henry Van Porter , a well-dressed , self-styled socialite who ridiculed the other characters on the '' Amos 'n' Andy '' television show , he and other members of the cast were excoriated for demeaning depictions of blacks . <br><blue>16</blue>Civil rights groups forced the show off the air after the 1953 season . '' <br><blue>17</blue>We had a hard time then fighting for dignity , '' he said later . '' <br><blue>18</blue>We had no power . <br><blue>19</blue>We had to take it , and because we took it , the young people today have greater opportunities . '' <br><blue>20</blue>Mr. Hairston 's wife , Isabelle Margaret Swanigan , died in 1986 . <br><hr><br><blue>1(32)</blue>: <m_str>he</m_str> (15_3) 	<m_str>His</m_str> (4_1) 	<m_str>Mr. Hairston</m_str> (7_13) 	<m_str>him</m_str> (7_17) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (8_1) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (4_6) 	<m_str>himself</m_str> (8_3) 	<m_str>Sidney Poitier</m_str> (10_32) 	<m_str>Mr. Hairston</m_str> (12_1) 	<m_str>the composer Dimitri Tiomkin</m_str> (4_8) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (12_4) 	<m_str>Mr. Hairston 's</m_str> (20_1) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (9_1) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (15_32) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (2_1) 	<m_str>Mr. Tiomkin</m_str> (5_15) 	<m_str>Mr. Tiomkin</m_str> (9_12) 	<m_str>I</m_str> (6_1) 	<m_str>I</m_str> (5_21) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (10_1) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (17_12) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (13_17) 	<m_str>Mr. Hairston</m_str> (6_8) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (14_1) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (10_6) 	<m_str>I</m_str> (6_13) 	<m_str>Mr. Hairston</m_str> (3_1) 	<m_str>you</m_str> (6_19) 	<m_str>Mr. Tiomkin</m_str> (7_1) 	<m_str>my</m_str> (6_21) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (10_18) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (11_1) 	<br><blue>2(4)</blue>: <m_str>We</m_str> (17_1) 	<m_str>We</m_str> (18_1) 	<m_str>We</m_str> (19_1) 	<m_str>we</m_str> (19_9) 	<br><blue>3(4)</blue>: <m_str>the show</m_str> (16_5) 	<m_str>it</m_str> 